data.enText: a chemical element. Nitrogen is a gas that is found in large quantities in the earth's atmosphere.

tr: a common nonmetallic element that is normally a colorless odorless tasteless inert diatomic gas
constitutes 78 percent of the atmosphere by volume
a constituent of all living tissues

value.def: Nitrogen is a colourless element that has no smell and is usually found as a gas. It forms about 78% of the earth's atmosphere, and is found in all living things.

trans: 氮循环(各种形式的氮在自然界的循环)
